  "market_context": "GBPUSD 5-minute chart on 27/12/2023, with price declining from around 1.27360 into the 1.27050 area, forming a swing structure suitable for identifying a bullish breaker block formation.",
  "key_observation": "A bullish breaker block forms once price prints a low, high, lower low, and then a higher high; the series of up-close candles between the initial low and high becomes the breaker block, expected to support price on retest.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the initial swing low forming on the GBPUSD 5-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Mark the subsequent swing high created after the low.",
    "Step 3: Wait for price to print and confirm a lower low below the initial low.",
    "Step 4: Confirm a higher high closing above the prior swing high, completing the low-high-lower low-higher high sequence.",
    "Step 5: Mark out the series of up-close candles between the initial low and high as the bullish breaker block zone.",
    "Step 6: Watch for price to return to the breaker block, sweep the prior low into the zone, and respect the bodies before continuing higher."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price retested the breaker block, swept the prior low into the zone with bodies still respecting the level, and continued higher as expected.",
  "lessons": "A valid bullish breaker block requires the full low-high-lower low-higher high sequence; the up-close candles between the initial low and high serve as the reaction zone where price is expected to find support on retest.",
